ails**: \n   - Use `always @(posedge clk)` for state transitions with synchronous `reset`.\n   - Use `always @(*)` for next-state logic.\n   - Use `localparam` for state encoding.\n   - Avoid `unique`, `inside`, or `state_t` per requirements.\n5. **Advice to avoid syntax errors**: \n   - Ensure all signals are declared as `logic`.\n   - Use `always @(*)` for combinational logic to avoid simulation-synthesis mismatches.\n   - Ensure the `reset` logic is correctly applied in the sequential block.",
